al experience for you. <strong>Make your reservations now.</strong> For booking click on the &quot;<strong>Official Ticket URL</strong>&quot; button.</span></span></p>', '2018-12-31', '2019-01-01', '15:00:00', '11:30:00', '1542651757.jpg', '1542651757.jpg', 19, '', 'https://packages.bmyraahi.com/package-detail-of-new-years-eve-event-2d1n/', 'https://packages.bmyraahi.com/', 'https://www.facebook.com/BmyRaahiofficial/', 'https://twitter.com/BmyRaahi', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/bmyraahi/', '', '', '', 0, 933, 1, 0, 2, 0, 1, 1, 'A', 0, '2018-11-20 01:22:37', '2018-12-06 00:34:31'),
(35, 'New Delhi World Book Fair 2019 at Pragati Maidan', 'new-delhi-world-book-fair-2019', 10, 0, '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The New Delhi World Book Fair (NDWBF) 2019 is just around the corner. It&rsquo;s not just a major calendar...</span></span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Does reading books make you happier? Well, there is good news for you! <strong>The New Delhi World Book Fair (NDWBF) 2019</strong> is just around the corner. It&rsquo;s not just a major calendar event for the authors and publishers but is equally popular among book readers. As the book industry in India is growing, NDWBF provides a unique trade opportunity for exhibitors along with the ideal platform for promoting titles. So, get ready to indulge into the best of publishing and intellectual worlds. Major publication houses from across the world are likely to exhibit their literary collections at the book fair 2019. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">In 2018, the fair attracted nearly <strong>1,000 exhibitors</strong> from India and over <strong>30 foreign exhibitors</strong>. This year, the fair is going to be even bigger with many literary and publishing programs and conferences lined up for the nine-day event starting from <strong>January 5, 2019, and ending on January 13, 2019</strong>.&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Organized by National Book Trust</strong>, India in association with Ministry of Human Resource Development, Department of Higher Education, Government of India, Bookfair is the ideal destination for those who just can&rsquo;t get over lively literary activities. Panel discussions, book launches, dialogues, and a lot more awaits you!</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The fair will feature books from all genres, be it Children Books, Sports Books, Fictions, Publications &amp; Journals, Magazines, International Books and even Old Books. Along with Authors Corners, there will be Children Pavilions and International Events Corner. </span></span></strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">While the theme of the 2018 edition of the NDWBF was &lsquo;Environment and Climate Change&rsquo;, this time it will be focused on &lsquo;Readers with Special Needs&rsquo;. The emphasis will be on the importance of inclusive learning and reading for children with special needs. There will be an exclusive exhibition of audio books, braille books, and other reading aids for differently-abled and children with ear or eye impairment. You can also find books related to children with ADHD, psychological and behavioral problems at the Theme pavilion to promote the habit of reading among them. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Save the date and book your calendar! Make sure you don&rsquo;t miss out on this fair, which is all about how interesting and empowering the reading can be.</span></span></p>', '2019-01-05', '2019-01-13', '11:00:00', '20:00:00', '1542796397.jpg', '1542796397.jpg', 22, '', 'http://www.newdelhiworldbookfair.gov.in/', 'http://www.newdelhiworldbookfair.gov.in/', 'https://www.facebook.com/NewDelhiWorldBookFair', 'https://twitter.com/ndworldbookfair', '', '', '', 'https://youtube.com/nbtindia', '', 0, 1637, 1, 1, 2, 0, 1, 1, 'A', 0, '2018-11-21 17:33:17', '2018-11-22 00:37:10'),
(36, 'TATA Mumbai Marathon 2019 (OVERSEAS RUNNER CRITERIA)', 'tata-mumbai-marathon-2019', 2, 0, '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Mumbai Marathon, which is now sponsored by the TATA group is scheduled to happen on 20 January 2019....</span></span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Mumbai Marathon</strong>, which is now sponsored by the TATA group is scheduled to happen on <strong>20 January 2019</strong>. It&rsquo;s time to cheer for a lifetime by running for a good cause. The marathon has its own fundraising platform managed by United Way Mumbai, which has successfully raised Rs 196 crore in association with 512 NGOs over the years. So, if you want to contribute to any social cause, all you need to do is choose an NGO and contribute. Remember, every penny count!</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">All fitness enthusiasts and amateur runners have a chance to come together and unfold the power of sports. Not just a sporting event, the marathon is also considered as an opportunity for people with varying abilities, caste, creed and social strata coming together for a good cause.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">All finishers of the full and half marathon will get a medal, and they can download <strong>Timing Certificates of Marathon</strong> Finisher within 21 days of the race day by going on the event website. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Participation in the <strong>Open 10K Run</strong> is open to those who are supporting any NGO which has registered for the event under United Way Mumbai. They will have to pay for the <strong>application fee of INR 1400 / USD 45 along with the charity amount</strong>. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Tata Mumbai Marathon is happening on</strong> January 20, 2019</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Distance and time cut-off:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><em>Full Marathon: (42.195 KM) </em></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Minimum age eligibility</strong>: 18 years as on race day (Born on or before January 19, 2001)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><em>Half Marathon: (21.097 KM) </em></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Minimum age eligibility</strong>: 18 years as on race day (Born on or before January 19, 2001)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><em>Open 10K Run: (10 KM)</em></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Minimum age eligibility</strong>: 15 years as on race day (Born on or before January 19, 2004)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><em>Dream Run: (6.6 KM)</em></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Minimum age eligibility</strong>: 12 years as on race day (Born on or before January 19, 2007)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><em>Senior Citizen&rsquo;s Run: (4.7 KM)</em></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Minimum age eligibility</strong>: 60 years as on race day (Born on or before January 19, 1959)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><em>Champions with Disability: (2.1 KM)</em></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Minimum age eligibility</strong>: 12 years as on race day (Born on or before January 19, 2007)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Application fee (inclusive of 18 percent GST)</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Domestic applicants: Rs 1,400</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Overseas applicants: USD 45</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>How to register?</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">For Registration: Click on &quot;<strong>Official Ticket URL</strong>&quot; button and&nbsp; Download the Marathon form and apply online</span></span></p>', '2019-01-20', '2019-01-20', '06:30:00', '10:00:00', '1542801367.jpg', '1542801306.jpg', 23, '', 'https://registration.procamrunning.in/tmm/registration.php', 'https://tatamumbaimarathon.procamrunning.in/', 'https://www.facebook.com/TataMumMarathon/', 'https://twitter.com/TataMumMarathon?lang=en', '', 'https://www.instagram.com/tatamummarathon/?hl=en', '', '', '', 0, 997, 1, 1, 2, 0, 1, 1, 'A', 0, '2018-11-21 18:55:06', '2018-11-23 01:21:46'),
(37, 'NCR Half Marathon 2nd Edition - Noida', 'ncr-half-marathon-2nd-edition-noida', 2, 0, '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The marathon will start from Decathlon at 6 am on 27 December 2018 and will continue till 9 am....</span></span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Looking for an event that will get your adrenaline pumping? NCR Half marathon is just for you! There are different race categories to chose from depending upon your age and interest. The marathon will start from Decathlon at 6 am on 27 January 2018 and will continue till 9 am.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">You can opt for categories like <strong>21.1 KM run, 10.5 KM run, 5 KM Couple Run &amp; 5 KM Fun Run</strong>. This is the second year of Marathon organized by <strong>K. V. NCR Maratho</strong>n. Expecting an immense participation from the residents of Delhi/ NCR, the second edition of this marathon is likely to be even more fun. It&rsquo;s considered as a social panacea where people from all walks of life come together to walk for good health. People from all age groups can participate in this event to show their commitment towards healthy and active living.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">All the participants at the <strong>NCR Half Marathon</strong> will get energy drinks, water, and first aid service to ensure that participants enjoy their run to the finishing point comfortably. To appreciate the enthusiasm of participants, organizers are planning to distribute the finisher medal and online timing certificate to those who touch the finishing line. Race result and certificates will be available on the website the very next day of the marathon. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Moreover, registered participants will get an email about BIB number, timing chips and they can collect T-shirts approximately one-week before the marathon date. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Reporting Time: 5:30 am</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>5 KM Run</strong>: Participants need to be at least 8 Years old&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>10.5 KM Run</strong>: Participants need to be at least 12 Years old</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>21.1 KM Run</strong>: Participants need to be at least 15 Years old</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">*Top 3 Runners (in Male &amp; Female Categories respectively) will Get Gifts &amp; Awards!</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>', '2019-01-27', '2019-01-27', '05:30:00', '09:30:00', '1542990778.jpg', '1542990778.jpg', 24, '', 'https://www.goeventz.com/event/ncr-half-marathon-2nd-edition/72976?utm_source=Festeve-mantra&utm_medium=sports-category&utm_campaign=Festeve-mantra-website-event', 'https://www.justplaysportz.com/event/ncr-half-marathon-2nd-edition', 'https://www.facebook.com/festevemantra/', 'https://twitter.com/festevemantra', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 326, 1, 1, 2, 0, 1, 1, 'A', 0, '2018-11-23 23:32:58', '2018-11-24 00:01:38'),
(38, 'New Year Celebration: Pawna Lakeside Camping', 'new-year-pawana-lakeside-Camping', 4, 0, '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Celebrate the New Year in Pawna Lakeside and ring in the year 2019 with great music, awesome food....</span></span></p>', '<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Celebrate the <strong>New Year in Pawna Lakeside</strong> and ring in the year 2019 with great music, awesome food, and a wonderful bonfire experience. Pawna Lake is located in Maval Taluka of Pawna district and is a serene camping side. Not just the New Year but the first day of the year 2019 will be equally beautiful, as you will wake up to the delightful Pawna Lake. Party hard all night, and relax during the daytime with a picturesque lakeside view. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Not just the Lake, but there are many other tourist attractions nearby to make your New Year plan with your loved ones memorable. You can walk through the memory lane and indulge in the splendors of the Indian History while taking a stroll at Tikona, Tung, Lohgad and Visapur fort. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><em>Who Can Be a Part of This Event?</em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Anyone who enjoy Camping and Bonfire beside Lake, and find good food just irresistible.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><em>Itinerary:</em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Day Welcome to our Campsite1 :&nbsp;</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Try reaching our <strong>Campsite by 4 pm</strong> (Conveyance to the campsite is not included in the package). You will get your own tents, where you can freshen up, unpack your bags and settle down as many exciting activities are lined up.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Evening Snacks/ Refreshments</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Around <strong>5: 30 pm, evening snacks, and hot tea</strong> will be served in our dining area. Enjoy the sunset while having refreshments and explore the campsite. Or, you can just sit by the lakeside and enjoy the whispering sound waves.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Bonfire &amp; Party Time </strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Around 8 pm, the <strong>Bonfire Session will start with a bang! Loud music and DJ </strong>will help you let loose yourself. No one is judging your dance steps, so just dance your heart out and enjoy the New Year party.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Dinner Time</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">It&rsquo;s time to feast! Dinner will be served around 9.15 PM, where you can enjoy local delicacies (Veg &amp; Non-Veg). Don&rsquo;t forget to fuel up yourself, as you have to re-join the party with unmatched enthusiasm and energy. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Day </strong>Happy New Year Guys!<strong>2 :&nbsp;</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Time to Make a Good Start</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Wake up around 6:30 am to the amazing view of the lake and the mesmerizing sunrise. The foggy view and the chilly wind around Pawna Lake will ensure a refreshing experience.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Breakfast is Ready</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">You can indulge in the delicious breakfast time around 9 am. Post Breakfast, the hard time will come when you will have to bid adieu to this awesome adventure spot!</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Package&nbsp;</span><strong>INR&nbsp;3750</strong>&nbsp;+ 5% GST per person* (&nbsp;To buy tickets click on the &quot;<strong>Official Ticket URL</strong>&quot; Button.)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Inclusions:</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Welcome Tea &amp; Snacks</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Dinner (Veg / N-Veg)</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Next day Breakfast</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Outdoor DJ</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Tent with Bedding and blanket, pillow</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Exclusions:</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">Traveling till Campsite</span> </span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">GST &amp; any personal expenses other than Inclusions</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Cancellation and refund applicable on the tour cost:</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">If cancellation is done prior to 15 days of outing 75% will be refunded.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">If done prior to 10 days of outing 50% will be refunded.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">After that, no refund will be provided.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:#333333\">Things to Carry:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Carry woolen clothes or jacket, muffler, shoes &amp;&nbsp;warm cap for the night</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Those who are not used to cold nights carry personal extra blankets. (We will be providing bed, cushion &amp; 1 pull over as part of the package)</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Torch with extra batteries - (Compulsory)</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Please carry id proof eg. Pan card, driving license</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in\">&nbsp;</p>', '2018-12-31', '2019-01-01', '16:00:00', '11:00:00', '1542994964.jpg', '1542994964.jpg', 25, '', 'https://www.meraevents.com/event/pawna-lake-new-year-camping-on-31st-1st-january-2019?acode=aAcuPF', 'https://www.smallstepsadventures.com/', 'https://www.facebook.com/smallstepsadventures', 'https://twitter.com/@SmallStepsIndia', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/small-steps-adventures', 'https://www.instagram.com/smallstepsadventures/', 'https://plus.google.com/+Smallstepsadventures', '', '', 0, 370, 1, 1, 2, 0, 1, 1, 'A', 0, '2018-11-24 00:42:44', '2018-12-06 00:36:56');
